FBIS4-6680 "dreas077__a94021" FBIS-EAS-94-077-A Daily Report 21 April 1994 ANNEX Mongolia Hunger Strike Against Government Continues Hunger Strike Against Government Continues Bourgeois Party Defends Government OW1904183194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1239 GMT 19 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1904183194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME English BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 19 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- This was released by the leader of the Mongolian Bourgeois Party [MBP] and owner of a large private "Buyan" company B. Jargalsaihan. In his interview to the Mongolian television he defined the stand of his party regarding the tense situation shaped down in the country due to a political hunger strike by representatives of the Mongolian Democratic Association (MDA) a number of opposition forces of the country demanding for resignation of the incumbent government. According to him, the government headed by P. Jasray is not to be blamed for all the economic and other hardships of the country. We should remember of the state of the country at the moment of its forming as well as the state of the national economy. If the demands of those participating in the hunger strike are associated with some certain persons their cases should be solved within the frameworks of the law, he pointed out. It is the conscious labour of every Mongolian, discipline, order and good arrangement and not empty words and mere declarations and political hunger strikes and chaos that will go out Mongolia from the economic crisis and destruction, considers B. Jargalsaihan. The leader of the MBP condemns the extremity of actions of the opposition forces arranging the current hunger strike.
